<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36097a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36097a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36097a"> 97(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> exhibit lights</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Of the name Castlesie]</font> &hellip; and &ldquo;size&rdquo;&mdash;doubtless a corruption of &ldquo;soillse&rdquo;, a light, would indicate that <mark>a light was, on dark and stormy nights, exhibited</mark> at some point on the river, to guide the travellers to the ford. <small> Weston St. John Joyce, <a name="WSJ1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WSJ1"><cite title="source">The Neighbourhood of Dublin</cite></a> (1921) 236-237</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
